2. Calculate the total dose of PAM required for the entire treatment period.
3. Convert the total dose from moles to grams.

Step 1: Calculate the total dose of PAM required per hour
\text{Hourly dose} = \text{Dose per kg} \times \text{Body mass}
\text{Hourly dose} = 3 \, \text{mmol kg}^{-1} \times 80 \, \text{kg} = 240 \, \text{mmol}

Step 2: Calculate the total dose of PAM required for the entire treatment period
\text{Total dose} = \text{Hourly dose} \times \text{Treatment duration}
\text{Total dose} = 240 \, \text{mmol} \times 24 \, \text{h} = 5760 \, \text{mmol}

Step 3: Convert the total dose from moles to grams
\text{Total mass} = \text{Total dose} \times \text{Molar mass}
\text{Total mass} = 5760 \, \text{mmol} \times 172.612 \, \text{g mol}^{-1}

\text{Total mass} = 5760 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{mol} \times 172.612 \, \text{g mol}^{-1} = 995.14272 \, \text{g}

Therefore, the mass of PAM required for an 80 kg person over a treatment period of 24 hours is:

\boxed{995.14272} \, \text{g}

