Since each lactic acid unit reacts with one \ce{KOH} molecule, the moles of lactic acid units are equal to the moles of \ce{KOH} used in the titration.
\begin{align*}
\text{moles of lactic acid units} &= \text{moles of}~\ce{KOH} \\
&= \pu{0.2724 mmol}
\end{align*}

Step 3: Calculate the average molar mass of the polymer chains
\begin{align*}
